Being in Caroling Cotton’s kitchen  getting my hair pressed when I wass a little girl was everything to me. “My ritual of passage!” She would even save all the Prince magazine’s so I could read all the articles and see all the pictures of him. Remembering moments of who I am and how  it’s cultivated in small gestures that create memories stamped in my brain. These memories are what we pull from in times of need to forge through our toughest times. 

Yesterday I went back to the  kitchen. I needed the gestures again that offered healing, conversation, knowledge and a since of peace and calmness. A hard look at how we need to do better be better. A moment away  from the storm. I reconnected to the culture we created out of nothing. 

When I left I couldn’t  help but think of Annie Malone and why the hot comb is still so important to us. This was a way for the working class women to care for themselves in ways they had never before. It offered a “woman’s class and social standing. 

Well anyway I said all this to say -Thanks Richard B.

I have been so excited about getting Morpheus8 @everbody, I could hardly keep it in. I have wanted this treatment for some time and researched it for a year prior to finally having it done. 

I started to see a loss in elasticity and subtle signs of aging. It seems small but these small things can become larger than life so I decided to just get a handle and improve my overall face and neck aesthetic. 

Morpheus8 is micro-needling with radio frequency technology to  stimulate collagen production to tighten & smooth wrinkles on the face and neck .

3 rounds of  treatment were customized to cater to my specific concerns.

I started to observe results after about 3 weeks of treatments and skin improves for up to 3 months.
